My Sister and I were there for three weeks in 1997, in Karachi, Islamabad, Lahore and two smaller towns up in the mountains, Multan and Bourbon. Your videos have brought back a lot of fond memories. You're right about everyone there being so polite; I remember during the last week we were there we had to turn down dinner invitations every day because we had previous dinner engagements that were arranged from the week prior. Also, how it's very common for men to hold hands over there. I'll never forget seeing two Pakistani traffic cops standing in the middle of a busy street, in uniform, holding hands. I loved the food, as well. Surprisingly, you will find some of the world's best Chinese food in Pakistan. This is a great idea, having influencers show another side of a country like Pakistan, as opposed to what the news media spoon feeds the public. Awesome video series, keep up the great work and, as always, safe travels!

Breathtaking sceneries, diverse landscape and culture, rich heritage, a history buff's dream come true and a foodie's absolute heaven. It's beautiful all over.
